<BaseLayout title="Maps" description="Public maps of Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts</p>
    <h1>Maps</h1>
    <p class="lede">Maps help readers understand place, relation, and route inside Vaelinya.</p>
    <p>A map can show boundary, nearness, distance, and how one place affects another. It helps the world feel travelled rather than abstract.</p>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">First map layer</p>
      <h2>Reader orientation</h2>
      <p>This first map layer gives a simple way to understand where reading and world ideas begin.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>The Rim</strong> — the edge-place and borderland.</li>
        <li><strong>The Rimaeri</strong> — the people of the Rim.</li>
        <li><strong>Lina</strong> — the clearest first story path into the world.</li>
        <li><strong>The Warm Remembering</strong> — a cultural thread of care, continuity, and shared remembrance.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Start with one route, then move outward.</p>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/world/the-rim/">Places of the world</a>
      <a href="/artefacts/story-objects/">Story objects</a>
      <a href="/read/lina/">Read Lina</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
